// Virtual main: exit code = code_a() + code_z() + code_e_acute_minus_200()
//                         == 65 + 122 + 33 == 220. Reaching it forces the WHOLE work.tks
// (the char type, `c'…'` literals ASCII + multibyte, the `char to u32` decode) through the
// checker, VM and codegen. A clean exit 220 on BOTH the VM (`teko run`) and the compiled
// binary (`teko build`) proves the char subsystem holds.
use m

(m::code_a() + m::code_z() + m::code_e_acute_minus_200()) to i32
